gomodel:SYNGO_3966  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Synaptogyrin localizes to synaptic vesicles. Immunogold labelling (Fig. 3) using a specific (Fig. 1) polyclonal rabbit antibody as well as subcellular fractionation experiments (Fig. 4) indicate the presence of Synaptogyrin (P29) on synaptic vesicles.. Experimental description: Synaptic vesicles were prepared essentially as described earlier (Nagy et al., 1976; Huttnor et aL, 1983; Jahn et al., 1985). Briefly, cerebral cortices of 20 rats were homogenized" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
